<span key="582da72b0a1444b78e616c5e1e9e5ce9"><span offset-key="582da72b0a1444b78e616c5e1e9e5ce9:0">What is a plugin?</span></span>

<span key="bd1a965d291e41f080104412761ade8d"><span offset-key="bd1a965d291e41f080104412761ade8d:0">Gatsby plugins are Node.js packages that implement Gatsby APIs and are commonly installed through a registry like npm. There are many types of </span></span><a href="https://www.gatsbyjs.com/plugins/" class="css-4rbku5 css-1dbjc4n r-1loqt21 r-1471scf r-1otgn73 r-1i6wzkk r-lrvibr"><span data-key="90dc09e80ef9489ab33d2b625a51b30c" data-rnw-int-class="nearest_257-3886_259-3887-237__"><span data-key="f8d56fdae3d740f49738c4aacea41ac5"><span data-offset-key="f8d56fdae3d740f49738c4aacea41ac5:0">plugins</span></span></span></a><span key="3be9f13853e343e1b643e574d65733f6"><span offset-key="3be9f13853e343e1b643e574d65733f6:0">, including data sourcing, SEO, responsive images, offline support, support for Sass, TypeScript, sitemaps and RSS, Google Analytics, and more. You can also </span></span><a href="https://www.gatsbyjs.com/docs/creating-plugins/" class="css-4rbku5 css-1dbjc4n r-1loqt21 r-1471scf r-1otgn73 r-1i6wzkk r-lrvibr"><span data-key="992b2591f1c2436e95a3275a8addefa9" data-rnw-int-class="nearest_257-3886_259-3887-237__"><span data-key="24ae68ecd292474fa82d7d124fb44cd7"><span data-offset-key="24ae68ecd292474fa82d7d124fb44cd7:0">make your own plugins</span></span></span></a><span key="a98af549e0494158a3cd3860c4147b65"><span offset-key="a98af549e0494158a3cd3860c4147b65:0"> and either distribute them for fellow Gatsby developers to use or </span></span><a href="https://www.gatsbyjs.com/docs/loading-plugins-from-your-local-plugins-folder/" class="css-4rbku5 css-1dbjc4n r-1loqt21 r-1471scf r-1otgn73 r-1i6wzkk r-lrvibr"><span data-key="94a68c8f358e4fe186726e61b2483510" data-rnw-int-class="nearest_257-3886_259-3887-237__"><span data-key="8a571a39e3824bbe83dd29318906364c"><span data-offset-key="8a571a39e3824bbe83dd29318906364c:0">install them locally</span></span></span></a><span key="35e996361a3f4d75a5e84b12c0d91a06"><span offset-key="35e996361a3f4d75a5e84b12c0d91a06:0">.</span></span>

## 

<span key="63618cc66a074e00a20d6b15403b7dc9"><span offset-key="63618cc66a074e00a20d6b15403b7dc9:0">What is a theme?</span></span>

<span key="8cc47ab810c945c1abda91a5311ad08a"><span offset-key="8cc47ab810c945c1abda91a5311ad08a:0">A Gatsby theme is a type of plugin that includes a </span>`gatsby-config.js`<span offset-key="8cc47ab810c945c1abda91a5311ad08a:2"> file and adds pre-configured functionality, data sourcing, and/or UI code to Gatsby sites. Since they are plugins, themes can be packaged and distributed through a registry like npm or yarn, and versions can be updated through a site’s </span>`package.json`<span offset-key="8cc47ab810c945c1abda91a5311ad08a:4"> file.</span></span>

<span key="89c91ae27b484777ac6b511075c2bf09"><span offset-key="89c91ae27b484777ac6b511075c2bf09:0">With a Gatsby theme, all of your default configuration (shared functionality, data sourcing, design) is abstracted out of your site and into an installable package. A theme might differ from a typical plugin in that it packages up usage of a plugin into a consumable API, making it possible to include functionality without having to type out all of the code by hand (such as GraphQL queries). To understand more of the motivation for Gatsby themes, check out the docs on </span></span><a href="https://www.gatsbyjs.com/docs/themes/what-are-gatsby-themes/" class="css-4rbku5 css-1dbjc4n r-1loqt21 r-1471scf r-1otgn73 r-1i6wzkk r-lrvibr"><span data-key="c5209a7d0d734acaab1094873b46bace" data-rnw-int-class="nearest_257-3886_259-3887-237__"><span data-key="d525739516184cd6ba54fae0f4e824c0"><span data-offset-key="d525739516184cd6ba54fae0f4e824c0:0">What are Gatsby Themes?</span></span></span></a><span key="e04cb3687eda44e681af9d8f5586b421"><span offset-key="e04cb3687eda44e681af9d8f5586b421:0"><span slate-zero-width="z">​</span></span></span>

## 

<span key="5cf1fea83a5549ad825e61971cadf221"><span offset-key="5cf1fea83a5549ad825e61971cadf221:0">What is a starter?</span></span>

<span key="3b8930ed9a4d457fa2a79a42eb504e74"><span offset-key="3b8930ed9a4d457fa2a79a42eb504e74:0">A starter is a boilerplate Gatsby site that users can copy and </span></span><a href="https://www.gatsbyjs.com/docs/modifying-a-starter/" class="css-4rbku5 css-1dbjc4n r-1loqt21 r-1471scf r-1otgn73 r-1i6wzkk r-lrvibr"><span data-key="8ab9ee6d134e41b2b579f3055dd45c69" data-rnw-int-class="nearest_257-3886_259-3887-237__"><span data-key="2d54da0857df4268916d36d6c1f41e16"><span data-offset-key="2d54da0857df4268916d36d6c1f41e16:0">customize</span></span></span></a><span key="9b57e0341b6b487ab6a6726d5f33dc00"><span offset-key="9b57e0341b6b487ab6a6726d5f33dc00:0">. Once modified, a starter maintains no connection to its source.</span></span>

<span key="97a1d239173042faab32d3e5bf0150b0"><span offset-key="97a1d239173042faab32d3e5bf0150b0:0">Gatsby offers </span></span><a href="https://www.gatsbyjs.com/docs/starters/#official-starters" class="css-4rbku5 css-1dbjc4n r-1loqt21 r-1471scf r-1otgn73 r-1i6wzkk r-lrvibr"><span data-key="53cefceade8e4c50af39fda3eb31a82f" data-rnw-int-class="nearest_257-3886_259-3887-237__"><span data-key="8ec7fe0d995f4b1f9f060c170266ea63"><span data-offset-key="8ec7fe0d995f4b1f9f060c170266ea63:0">official starters</span></span></span></a><span key="f501fed0a0ff4e5081a22cda6069c939"><span offset-key="f501fed0a0ff4e5081a22cda6069c939:0"> for a default site, blog site, bare-bones hello world site, and both using and creating themes. There are also many starters from members of the community that can provide a good starting point for your Gatsby site.</span></span>

## 

<span key="54e0f8f15a11451380694efe04145bfb"><span offset-key="54e0f8f15a11451380694efe04145bfb:0">Conventions for usage</span></span>

<span key="0396b7dbe24041c0ac4826f083dc6769"><span offset-key="0396b7dbe24041c0ac4826f083dc6769:0">Themes are a type of plugin, making both themes and plugins capable of the same functionality. The difference between them is </span>*intended usage*<span offset-key="0396b7dbe24041c0ac4826f083dc6769:2">. Themes are intended to own a piece of the site (like an about us page), whereas a plugin is intended to modularize Gatsby APIs into smaller pieces. Themes tend to cover a broader scope of responsibility, packaging up multiple behaviors, where plugins are meant for more specific functionality.</span></span>

<span key="bc3da4bff3d645c6b4ca89d0f33599b1"><span offset-key="bc3da4bff3d645c6b4ca89d0f33599b1:0">Starters are generally used as the starting point that plugins and themes are then installed into. However, they’re based on one-time use and do not get updated over time as plugins and themes do.</span></span>

<span key="814cff9f0899433598b3c8a220f99ded"><span offset-key="814cff9f0899433598b3c8a220f99ded:0">When it comes to maintaining a Gatsby site, plugins and themes offer a distinct advantage to starters by being distributed as packages. This means making changes in multiple Gatsby sites is done by a new install of an updated package upstream. It’s difficult to sync changes across multiple sites derived from the same starter.</span></span>

### 

<span key="a3093a39150448fe94d8a0785028dfc1"><span offset-key="a3093a39150448fe94d8a0785028dfc1:0">Differences and considerations in configuration</span></span>

<span key="cfaee20ee1494bba9341ad2483934829"><span offset-key="cfaee20ee1494bba9341ad2483934829:0">Plugins and themes can expose options to make them configurable for users. There are different possibilities for configuration like passing in options and shadowing files that make plugins and themes more powerful—but also more complicated—than starters. Because themes are also plugins, shadowing is possible in plugins as well. It may make sense for a plugin to take advantage of the shadowing API, but it is less common.</span></span>

<span key="fafd90698c8840fc952a25aa00a755d7"><span offset-key="fafd90698c8840fc952a25aa00a755d7:0">◐</span></span>

<span key="37673bd4114e4a4cb06bb8af8a1aa461"><span offset-key="37673bd4114e4a4cb06bb8af8a1aa461:0">●</span></span>

<span key="e684039997694c02b113d3bbc9ce7d9a"><span offset-key="e684039997694c02b113d3bbc9ce7d9a:0">○</span></span>

<span key="4cf01184f55a4c62b70c6d38520c7b19"><span offset-key="4cf01184f55a4c62b70c6d38520c7b19:0">Uses Multiple Plugins</span></span>

<span key="c896ce0ac6d54a5bae5c9e98ac85d16f"><span offset-key="c896ce0ac6d54a5bae5c9e98ac85d16f:0">◐</span></span>

<span key="fd927e63a71c45c9bb1c7aec838df7fc"><span offset-key="fd927e63a71c45c9bb1c7aec838df7fc:0">●</span></span>

<span key="29db33d67a22408a91df196bf3f655be"><span offset-key="29db33d67a22408a91df196bf3f655be:0">●</span></span>

<span key="bdef6a5e13bf4e67a89fdd767ec34591"><span offset-key="bdef6a5e13bf4e67a89fdd767ec34591:0">Custom components</span></span>

<span key="94a7864ef3a8437b8eee6f33a7caaadd"><span offset-key="94a7864ef3a8437b8eee6f33a7caaadd:0">◐</span></span>

<span key="e9df7e3314e94bbead7b951c9248cf0b"><span offset-key="e9df7e3314e94bbead7b951c9248cf0b:0">●</span></span>

<span key="2fa9b44cf6f547ceb70ae8391b5f4184"><span offset-key="2fa9b44cf6f547ceb70ae8391b5f4184:0">●</span></span>

<span key="63bcfb7d340a43a293a61b39b9696d76">**Pass in Options**</span>

<span key="73ed261833e74903a87170d67574f564"><span offset-key="73ed261833e74903a87170d67574f564:0">Plugins and themes both allow options to be passed in when installed in the plugins array of a </span>`gatsby-config`<span offset-key="73ed261833e74903a87170d67574f564:2">. Starters can be set up with documented options for customization, but there are no officially supported options for starters apart from what the author of the starter decides to write.</span></span>

<span key="246e7ea733414eb2a738ae75d3aeaf31">**Shadowing**</span>

<span key="366bcd0e659f436e8b4bf6d297499467"><span offset-key="366bcd0e659f436e8b4bf6d297499467:0">Theme </span></span><a href="https://www.gatsbyjs.com/docs/how-to/plugins-and-themes/shadowing/" class="css-4rbku5 css-1dbjc4n r-1loqt21 r-1471scf r-1otgn73 r-1i6wzkk r-lrvibr"><span data-key="51cf82f53b8f432691502ce8e7a4627e" data-rnw-int-class="nearest_257-3886_259-3887-237__"><span data-key="5062b9908b3541f8b7b2dd5babe01193"><span data-offset-key="5062b9908b3541f8b7b2dd5babe01193:0">shadowing</span></span></span></a><span key="1584f0e3a4e448f199f309bbc514431c"><span offset-key="1584f0e3a4e448f199f309bbc514431c:0"> exists to allow users to override or otherwise extend individual components provided by a theme. For example, a plugin or theme can provide a specific path to </span>`gatsby-config`<span offset-key="1584f0e3a4e448f199f309bbc514431c:2"> so the plugin knows where to build pages from, but the user wouldn’t be able adjust </span>*how*<span offset-key="1584f0e3a4e448f199f309bbc514431c:4"> those pages are built, only from what path. Theme shadowing allows users to replace a file with their own version of it, allowing them to rewrite that logic to use the path in a different way.</span></span>

<span key="3f9ed829508b419dbefd5066feaf8bcd"><span offset-key="3f9ed829508b419dbefd5066feaf8bcd:0">An example of a plugin that uses shadowing is </span></span><a href="https://www.gatsbyjs.com/plugins/gatsby-plugin-theme-ui/?=theme-ui#customizing-the-theme" class="css-4rbku5 css-1dbjc4n r-1loqt21 r-1471scf r-1otgn73 r-1i6wzkk r-lrvibr"><span data-key="f2ce5c0127474c5b9012057a688d7c4a" data-rnw-int-class="nearest_257-3886_259-3887-237__"><span data-key="7940a84b55ea4299a3eedeae3bf317dc"><code class="r-1vckr1u r-z2wwpe r-uibjmv r-m2pi6t r-1hvjb8t" data-slate-leaf="true" data-offset-key="7940a84b55ea4299a3eedeae3bf317dc:0">gatsby-plugin-theme-ui</code></span></span></a><span key="d8f87a226be04ca088c174beca339368"><span offset-key="d8f87a226be04ca088c174beca339368:0"> which allows you to shadow a theme file to use in your own theme.</span></span>

<span key="facd4152ac5249d09aa05999372f332f"><span offset-key="facd4152ac5249d09aa05999372f332f:0">Starters aren’t capable of shadowing (and they don’t need to be), because a user of a starter can adjust any file by editing it directly.</span></span>

<span key="6d2521d914264a2896884b1a9db5e2eb">**Uses multiple plugins**</span>

<span key="0ea38d9ccfb545369ee8a2b89bb0802d"><span offset-key="0ea38d9ccfb545369ee8a2b89bb0802d:0">Themes are intended to abstract several plugins into one, by making a </span>`gatsby-config`<span offset-key="0ea38d9ccfb545369ee8a2b89bb0802d:2"> that a Gatsby site will run along with its own config. Starters can also be configured with multiple plugins so someone can get up and running without worrying about configuring too many loose ends.</span></span>

<span key="87cbe4ddacd942d29c36eea0bf0dba47">**Custom components**</span>

<span key="b338ad46624a458a9a63dfdd62833ec0"><span offset-key="b338ad46624a458a9a63dfdd62833ec0:0">Custom components are most traditionally distributed as packages in the React ecosystem. Components don’t need to hook into the Gatsby build system, so if shipped with a plugin they don’t need to be included in a </span>`gatsby-config`<span offset-key="b338ad46624a458a9a63dfdd62833ec0:2">’s plugin array. This is the case with </span>`gatsby-image`<span offset-key="b338ad46624a458a9a63dfdd62833ec0:4"> which is a React component. It doesn’t need to be included in the plugins array because it is merely a component.</span></span>

<span key="88e13ed969aa42958f52eb224ab77219"><span offset-key="88e13ed969aa42958f52eb224ab77219:0">Some plugins ship with components you can use in a Gatsby site. An example is the </span></span><a href="https://www.gatsbyjs.com/plugins/gatsby-plugin-google-analytics/?=#outboundlink-component" class="css-4rbku5 css-1dbjc4n r-1loqt21 r-1471scf r-1otgn73 r-1i6wzkk r-lrvibr"><span data-key="b6e83a9b84d9418187edb0da69fe22c4" data-rnw-int-class="nearest_257-3886_259-3887-237__"><span data-key="6fe68e8258f7416aac455ae6cc05684f"><code class="r-1vckr1u r-z2wwpe r-uibjmv r-m2pi6t r-1hvjb8t" data-slate-leaf="true" data-offset-key="6fe68e8258f7416aac455ae6cc05684f:0">&lt;OutboundLink /&gt;</code><span data-offset-key="6fe68e8258f7416aac455ae6cc05684f:1">component from</span><code class="r-1vckr1u r-z2wwpe r-uibjmv r-m2pi6t r-1hvjb8t" data-slate-leaf="true" data-offset-key="6fe68e8258f7416aac455ae6cc05684f:2">gatsby-plugin-google-analytics</code></span></span></a><span key="15c7fd0d83ad450fa5f67492da49d6d7"><span offset-key="15c7fd0d83ad450fa5f67492da49d6d7:0">. Other plugins, like </span></span><a href="https://www.gatsbyjs.com/plugins/gatsby-plugin-react-helmet" class="css-4rbku5 css-1dbjc4n r-1loqt21 r-1471scf r-1otgn73 r-1i6wzkk r-lrvibr"><span data-key="fa2d36f9e8684455b2f7cc43d983816a" data-rnw-int-class="nearest_257-3886_259-3887-237__"><span data-key="07756201088c40848b04cbcbef915865"><code class="r-1vckr1u r-z2wwpe r-uibjmv r-m2pi6t r-1hvjb8t" data-slate-leaf="true" data-offset-key="07756201088c40848b04cbcbef915865:0">gatsby-plugin-react-helmet</code></span></span></a><span key="fde572855ab949c3abbfe9bd61786d39"><span offset-key="fde572855ab949c3abbfe9bd61786d39:0">, require you to install components from other libraries.</span></span>

<span key="6dd5f43c01fc4bf893fbff0230d84342"><span offset-key="6dd5f43c01fc4bf893fbff0230d84342:0">Themes by convention are more suited to ship with components that could then be shadowed for customization.</span></span>

<span key="762c3e8c5fb74ff184d1804ad459c12f"><span offset-key="762c3e8c5fb74ff184d1804ad459c12f:0">Starters will include components to render data, but they are tied to the starter.</span></span>

Deciding which to use
